WEBVTT

00:10.063 --> 00:11.391
What? Hello. There's...

00:11.907 --> 00:14.354
Don't you worry. It's only me.

00:18.256 --> 00:21.922
There is no such thing
as only you, Kimberly.

00:21.923 --> 00:22.726
Mm?

00:22.727 --> 00:25.851
Boy, this is bizarre.
It's not my birthday.

00:25.852 --> 00:27.618
Mnh-mnh. You're not
holding a cake.

00:31.454 --> 00:32.017
Mm.

00:32.018 --> 00:33.074
You lock the door?

00:33.518 --> 00:34.384
No.

00:36.463 --> 00:37.230
Oh!

00:37.534 --> 00:40.111
Oh, gosh. Oh. Oh. I am so sorry.

00:40.182 --> 00:45.214
I'm so sorry! Justin,
is the bar set up for the lunch rush?

00:45.215 --> 00:46.886
Uh, you know, not yet.

00:46.887 --> 00:49.607
I was looking for olives,
but we're out,

00:49.667 --> 00:51.365
uh, so I was just
trying to get some.

00:51.366 --> 00:54.529
Well, you know, time's wastin',
so chop chop.

00:54.530 --> 00:56.723
Yep. Be right there. All right.

00:59.455 --> 01:00.288
Oh!

01:08.146 --> 01:11.570
That ignorant, small-minded,
friggin' Neanderthal!

01:11.799 --> 01:12.694
Well, technically,

01:12.695 --> 01:14.743
it's pronounced "neander-tall."

01:16.550 --> 01:17.699
And you must have finally met

01:17.700 --> 01:20.243
our very own Giddrick Reischel.

01:20.415 --> 01:22.015
Huh. Yeah.

01:22.927 --> 01:25.081
I-I-I foolishly listened

01:25.082 --> 01:27.693
to his stupid, right-wing,
call-in show

01:27.694 --> 01:28.950
last night on the
way home from work,

01:28.951 --> 01:31.923
and it was filled with l...
I mean filled with lies...

01:31.963 --> 01:34.706
lies about global warming,
lies about immigration,

01:34.707 --> 01:35.734
lies about health care.

01:35.735 --> 01:37.982
And so right now in the hallway,
I-I-I ran into him,

01:37.983 --> 01:39.012
and I thought I would set

01:39.013 --> 01:41.249
him straight about a
few facts. Oh, Nora.

01:41.250 --> 01:44.206
You can't believe the
vile things he said to me.

01:44.207 --> 01:45.525
Well, you can't
take it personally.

01:45.526 --> 01:46.893
He's like that with everybody.

01:46.894 --> 01:48.777
How can I not
take it personally?

01:48.778 --> 01:51.067
He called my show "ask madam Mao."

01:52.060 --> 01:54.345
Ooh! Would you care
for some coffee?

01:54.346 --> 01:57.098
No. No, thank you.
Um, look, sit down.

02:03.799 --> 02:04.729
Take a breath.

02:06.281 --> 02:07.750
Now do you know who

02:07.751 --> 02:10.375
the two biggest advertisers
are on his show?

02:10.467 --> 02:11.373
Haven't a clue.

02:11.374 --> 02:13.377
Laser beam home security systems

02:13.378 --> 02:16.401
and herbal-firm male
potency pills. Ah.

02:16.402 --> 02:18.553
Now as a trained psychotherapist,

02:18.554 --> 02:21.563
that tells me two things
about him and his audience...

02:21.818 --> 02:23.609
Paranoid personality type

02:23.610 --> 02:27.482
with accompanying morbid
insecurity disorder.

02:30.684 --> 02:32.698
Talking to you always
makes me feel better.

02:33.083 --> 02:35.978
Oh. That's what friends
are for, right?

02:36.971 --> 02:37.920
Right.

02:40.918 --> 02:41.878
Okay.

02:44.375 --> 02:46.225
You know, I was just
reading here in the paper,

02:46.226 --> 02:49.354
there's a-a documentary
about Leonard Bernstein

02:49.355 --> 02:51.323
on public television tonight.

02:51.607 --> 02:55.111
Oh, my God. I have been in
love with him since I was 20.

02:55.247 --> 02:57.390
Well, would you like to come
over and watch it with me?

02:58.203 --> 02:59.161
At your house?

02:59.162 --> 03:02.523
Yeah. I-I just got this, uh,
this big screen television.

03:02.954 --> 03:05.787
I mean, we'll be able to
see the entire orchestra.

03:06.335 --> 03:08.254
Well, how could I say no?

03:08.994 --> 03:09.762
What time?

03:10.058 --> 03:13.691
Well, it starts at 10:00,
so, uh, 9:45?

03:15.223 --> 03:16.151
Perfect.

03:17.607 --> 03:18.582
Perfect.

03:19.233 --> 03:22.594
He invited you at 9:45
for a 10:00 TV show?

03:22.595 --> 03:23.506
Well, he's a shrink.

03:23.507 --> 03:26.349
Maybe he's only comfortable
in 45-minute increments.

03:26.350 --> 03:28.072
I know you wanna take
this to the next level.

03:28.073 --> 03:29.850
I don't think that
even counts as a level.

03:29.851 --> 03:33.897
That's like the elevator stalled
between floors. We did agree

03:33.898 --> 03:35.649
to be friends early on. Mom,

03:35.650 --> 03:37.706
you love your job.
You enjoy Karl's company.

03:37.707 --> 03:39.257
If you get into a
romantic relationship,

03:39.258 --> 03:41.218
and one of you gets hurt,
then you've lost a friend

03:41.219 --> 03:42.754
and screwed up your
work situation.

03:42.755 --> 03:45.006
What if he is actually
the man of my dreams,

03:45.007 --> 03:47.557
and... and I miss my chance?
You know what?

03:47.558 --> 03:48.901
I'm in over my head.
Why don't you ask Sarah?

03:48.902 --> 03:51.305
Well, I can't ask Sarah.
If this deal goes through,

03:51.306 --> 03:53.574
then she'll be my boss.
She'll be his boss.

03:53.575 --> 03:55.509
Mom, I gotta go. I'm sorry.
I'm hosting lunch,

03:55.510 --> 03:58.727
and I've accidentally overbooked
the reservations. Where's Saul?

03:59.085 --> 04:00.506
Wine convention, Napa.

04:00.507 --> 04:02.857
And since this is Justin's first
double shift behind the bar,

04:02.858 --> 04:04.535
and I clearly have no
idea what I'm doing,

04:04.962 --> 04:06.577
Scotty's a little
freaked out. Honey,

04:06.578 --> 04:08.734
well, just pretend you
have people skills.

04:09.182 --> 04:10.800
Uh, I-I gotta go.

04:10.888 --> 04:12.529
Talk to you later. Bye, mom.

04:12.530 --> 04:15.486
Um, Angie, have you met my brother Kevin?
Uh, nice to meet you.

04:15.487 --> 04:18.510
Nice to meet you. My God,
your hands are cold. You okay?

04:18.511 --> 04:21.646
We were in the walk-in
cooler for a while.

04:22.801 --> 04:24.854
Getting beer. Yeah.
It can take a while.

04:24.855 --> 04:25.781
You don't want to startle the beer

04:25.782 --> 04:28.868
by moving it too fast.
I should get back to the kitchen.

04:28.869 --> 04:31.000
I'll come with you.
Talk to you later.

04:31.105 --> 04:31.746
Bye, sweetie.

04:31.747 --> 04:32.531
Talk to you later.

